HEADWORD: Rhodosperm
<hw>Rho"do*sperm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"ro`don</grk> the rose + <grk>spe`rma</grk> a seed.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any seaweed with red spores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ As the name of a subclass, <xex>Rhodosperms</xex>, or
<spn>Rhodospermeae</spn>, is synonymous with <spn>Florideae</spn> (which
see.)</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhomb</ent>⟦br⟧
